Question: 
If the destructor is not called before exit. 
Is the Object cleaned up?
Will Valgrind test show memory leak?

Valgrind test: 
(a) exit from main(), where object was instantiated
(b) exit from function b(), bypass normal cleanup process.

/*************** Test code ********************************************/
/***** /home/sthiagar/42/cpp0/sample/destructor_cleanup_test.cpp *****/

#include <iostream>

class Apple {
public:
    Apple() {
        std::cout << "Apple created" << std::endl;
    }
    ~Apple() {
        std::cout << "Apple destroyed" << std::endl;
    }
};

void b() {
    std::cout << "Inside function b()" << std::endl;
    std::exit(0); // (b) Program exits here
}

int main() {
    Apple myApple; // Apple object instantiated here
    b(); // Calling function b()
    return 0; // a) Exiting main()
}
